HEADWORD: Isodrome
<hw>I"so*drome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> +
Gr. <?/ course.]</ety> <fld>(Nav.)</fld> <def>A method of moving a fleet
from one formation to another, the direction usually being changed eight
points (90⟦deg⟧), by means of paths of equal length for each ship. It is
prohibited in the United States navy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

